1
00:00:00,313 --> 00:00:01,966
That's a very chic name.

2
00:00:02,600 --> 00:00:03,640
What does it mean?

3
00:00:04,688 --> 00:00:07,400
Once upon a time, I had a dream.

4
00:00:15,040 --> 00:00:16,280
And... Action!

5
00:00:16,280 --> 00:00:18,475
When I was a kid,
I loved traditional dance.

6
00:00:18,475 --> 00:00:20,499
I wanted to be a star.

7
00:00:22,416 --> 00:00:24,162
Are you waiting for me, hmm?

8
00:00:24,995 --> 00:00:27,880
We've run into
each other a lot lately.

9
00:00:29,680 --> 00:00:33,840
Does that mean Charcoal doesn't
have to find a new home anymore?

10
00:00:59,524 --> 00:01:01,322
Why does it hurt this much?

11
00:01:05,305 --> 00:01:07,458
How am I supposed
to sleep with this pain?

12
00:01:10,739 --> 00:01:13,040
All my so-called lovers are gone.

13
00:01:15,320 --> 00:01:17,187
Once they got my money,
they just dumped me.

14
00:01:18,802 --> 00:01:20,600
Leaving me here
to rot in my own mess.

15
00:01:26,480 --> 00:01:28,406
I definitely won't
be able to sleep tonight.

16
00:01:39,738 --> 00:01:41,938
I can't sleep like this.

17
00:02:13,280 --> 00:02:14,720
So nice.

18
00:02:19,160 --> 00:02:20,160
Good.

19
00:02:20,740 --> 00:02:24,886
Your legs are hurting, aren't they?

20
00:02:25,440 --> 00:02:27,700
You can't stop
wandering around, can you?

21
00:02:30,063 --> 00:02:31,063
Look,

22
00:02:31,403 --> 00:02:33,977
If you won't stop complaining,
just leave me alone.

23
00:02:33,977 --> 00:02:36,857
I can massage myself.
Don't touch me.

24
00:02:36,857 --> 00:02:38,440
Be real, Mom.

25
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:41,800
That just means
she wants me to massage her.

26
00:02:42,839 --> 00:02:44,446
So, please keep going.

27
00:02:47,160 --> 00:02:49,340
Honestly, just a simple massage
for your mother.

28
00:02:49,340 --> 00:02:52,187
Think of all those
home-cooked meals

29
00:02:52,187 --> 00:02:54,240
I raised you with
for all those years.

30
00:02:54,240 --> 00:02:56,040
It's not too much to ask, is it?

31
00:02:56,764 --> 00:02:59,400
Other people's kids
take care of their parents

32
00:02:59,400 --> 00:03:02,110
and pamper them more than this,
I'm telling you.

33
00:03:03,458 --> 00:03:04,758
- Mom.
- What?

34
00:03:04,758 --> 00:03:07,625
- You should try some new friends.
- Why?

35
00:03:07,625 --> 00:03:11,584
the ones where their kids
abandon their parents.

36
00:03:12,280 --> 00:03:14,012
So you'll feel good

37
00:03:14,012 --> 00:03:17,779
that I'm actually here visiting
and massaging you like this.

38
00:03:18,800 --> 00:03:22,855
And even better
that you have me nearby.

39
00:03:23,433 --> 00:03:26,080
Ikkyu, time for bed.

40
00:03:26,680 --> 00:03:29,640
You have to go to school
earlier than usual tomorrow.

41
00:03:30,720 --> 00:03:34,000
Just one more round of lotion,
and I'm ready for bed.

42
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:35,240
Hmm...

43
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:40,013
You too, Ohn. Go home.
It'll be hard to find a ride later.

44
00:03:40,013 --> 00:03:42,155
And Mom, try to stay home for once.

45
00:03:42,827 --> 00:03:44,680
You're not well but
you keep wandering around.

46
00:03:45,040 --> 00:03:48,780
The doctor warned you that
your muslces are weakened.

47
00:03:48,780 --> 00:03:52,200
Be very careful when walking.
Just chat on the app.

48
00:03:52,200 --> 00:03:54,840
It's not as fun as seeing them
in person, right Grandma?

49
00:03:54,840 --> 00:03:56,040
I know how it is.

50
00:03:56,040 --> 00:03:59,520
You are so right,
my own flesh and blood.

51
00:04:00,872 --> 00:04:01,872
But Mom...

52
00:04:02,621 --> 00:04:05,622
try cutting down
on the walking, okay?

53
00:04:06,403 --> 00:04:09,640
Or the doctor is going to scold you
when you go for your check-up.

54
00:04:10,364 --> 00:04:11,440
Yeah, yeah.

55
00:04:12,439 --> 00:04:13,464
Such a nagger.

56
00:04:13,793 --> 00:04:17,786
See? Jee is calling you.
Go home, Ohn.

57
00:04:20,560 --> 00:04:22,800
He is always checking up on me.

58
00:04:23,513 --> 00:04:26,073
Well, that's what happens
when you're this lovable.

59
00:04:26,667 --> 00:04:27,667
Whatever!

60
00:04:32,503 --> 00:04:34,800
- It's not Uncle Jee.
- Oh!

61
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:36,120
It's Auntie Chon.

62
00:04:36,788 --> 00:04:37,788
Ouu...

63
00:04:41,880 --> 00:04:42,880
What's up?

64
00:04:44,515 --> 00:04:45,515
What?

65
00:04:46,085 --> 00:04:47,711
Okay. I'll head over right now.

66
00:05:08,443 --> 00:05:10,516
Nidnoi and I went out
for a papaya salad

67
00:05:10,516 --> 00:05:13,200
at a popular place
near Mae Champi's room.

68
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:18,400
The light is on.

69
00:05:19,400 --> 00:05:20,400
Come on.

70
00:05:21,861 --> 00:05:24,017
So we bought some congee for her.

71
00:05:28,025 --> 00:05:29,240
Why is it so quiet?

72
00:05:31,068 --> 00:05:32,155
Maybe she is sleeping.

73
00:05:32,155 --> 00:05:34,600
Yeah, she might be asleep.

74
00:05:38,360 --> 00:05:39,360
Hey!

75
00:05:41,320 --> 00:05:42,320
- Mae!
- Mae!

76
00:05:47,033 --> 00:05:50,720
We found her collapsed
on the floor in a pool of blood.

77
00:05:53,677 --> 00:05:55,120
- Amen to that.
- Amen to that.

78
00:05:55,826 --> 00:05:56,893
It's a blessing

79
00:05:56,893 --> 00:05:59,200
that you suddenly craved
papaya salad late at night

80
00:05:59,200 --> 00:06:01,360
without caring
about your acid reflux.

81
00:06:01,360 --> 00:06:02,400
Mmm.

82
00:06:02,400 --> 00:06:04,000
And thanks to Nidnoi, too,

83
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:06,933
for calling
the 1669 ambulance in time.

84
00:06:06,933 --> 00:06:09,440
And for giving Mae Champi
first aid before they arrived.

85
00:06:09,860 --> 00:06:10,893
Mmm.

86
00:06:10,893 --> 00:06:12,400
- Amen to that.
- Amen to that.

87
00:06:13,203 --> 00:06:14,400
Is she going to be okay?

88
00:06:15,216 --> 00:06:17,266
As far as we know,
she has a bump on her head.

89
00:06:17,680 --> 00:06:19,720
As for the blood,
it likely came from her vomiting.

90
00:06:20,600 --> 00:06:22,000
At first, I was terrified.

91
00:06:22,520 --> 00:06:24,360
I thought
she had turned into a zombie!

92
00:06:24,360 --> 00:06:26,100
There was blood
at the corners of her mouth.

93
00:06:26,100 --> 00:06:27,920
Good thing Nidnoi
snapped me out of it.

94
00:06:28,935 --> 00:06:30,775
- Amen to that...
- Stop that!

95
00:06:30,775 --> 00:06:32,668
- What?
- Are you saying "Amen" to that?

96
00:06:32,668 --> 00:06:34,109
You're unbelievable.

97
00:06:34,761 --> 00:06:37,108
We'll wait for Nidnoi
to finish talking to the doctor.

98
00:06:49,353 --> 00:06:50,880
Let's go home for today.

99
00:06:50,880 --> 00:06:52,240
- Huh?
- Why?

100
00:06:53,712 --> 00:06:56,720
We have to wait for a specialist
to examine her tomorrow anyway.

101
00:06:56,720 --> 00:06:58,720
But for now, she's out of danger.

102
00:07:01,560 --> 00:07:04,520
We still don't know
what's wrong with her, right?

103
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:06,852
Not yet.

104
00:07:06,852 --> 00:07:11,505
But judging from the symptoms,
there's a mass under her ribs

105
00:07:11,505 --> 00:07:14,800
along with dark urine,
jaundice, and yellow eyes.

106
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:16,986
She has abdominal swelling
and was vomiting blood.

107
00:07:18,950 --> 00:07:20,551
From everything...

108
00:07:22,440 --> 00:07:24,080
Mae likely has...

109
00:07:25,080 --> 00:07:26,680
terminal liver cancer.

110
00:07:27,280 --> 00:07:28,473
- Not true!
- Not true!

111
00:07:28,473 --> 00:07:29,727
I'm afraid it is.

112
00:07:29,727 --> 00:07:32,080
But she never had cirrhosis.

113
00:07:32,606 --> 00:07:34,640
She gave up alcohol
a long time ago,

114
00:07:34,640 --> 00:07:36,740
even the rice whisky.

115
00:07:36,740 --> 00:07:39,673
She isn't obese and
doesn't have fatty liver disease.

116
00:07:40,200 --> 00:07:43,160
We even forbid her
from eating peanuts

117
00:07:43,160 --> 00:07:45,408
or dried chilies
that might have aflatoxin,

118
00:07:45,408 --> 00:07:47,148
which causes liver cancer.

119
00:07:47,561 --> 00:07:51,228
And none of her relatives
have ever had liver cancer either.

120
00:07:51,228 --> 00:07:53,594
- Isn't that right?
- Mmm.

121
00:07:59,360 --> 00:08:00,562
Sorry, Doctor, but...

122
00:08:00,587 --> 00:08:03,433
if none of her relatives
have liver cancer

123
00:08:03,433 --> 00:08:04,446
then...

124
00:08:04,446 --> 00:08:06,373
How did she get liver cancer?

125
00:08:06,373 --> 00:08:08,640
Well, the cause stems from...

126
00:08:08,640 --> 00:08:12,280
My old partner he had hepatitis.

127
00:08:12,979 --> 00:08:14,212
- What?
- What?

128
00:08:15,916 --> 00:08:18,996
The guy you quit
your job to live with?

129
00:08:18,996 --> 00:08:21,682
The one who gambled,
drank, cheated, and hit you?

130
00:08:22,189 --> 00:08:24,755
He conned you
and then abandoned you.

131
00:08:25,693 --> 00:08:28,373
Yes, he left me.

132
00:08:29,690 --> 00:08:32,343
And he left me
with Hepatitis B, too.

133
00:08:35,560 --> 00:08:38,440
In Mae Champi's case,
the cause of the cancer

134
00:08:38,440 --> 00:08:41,440
is the Hepatitis B infection.

135
00:08:42,440 --> 00:08:44,680
And what is the treatment plan?

136
00:08:45,440 --> 00:08:48,400
I need to discuss this
with the patient as well.

137
00:08:49,920 --> 00:08:51,040
What do you mean?

138
00:08:51,680 --> 00:08:55,320
Well, the disease
has reached its final stage.

139
00:08:57,880 --> 00:09:00,040
And given your advanced age,

140
00:09:00,690 --> 00:09:05,560
I'm concerned that
treating you with chemotherapy...

141
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:08,640
Are there any other options?

142
00:09:10,760 --> 00:09:11,760
Well...

143
00:09:14,720 --> 00:09:16,600
I don't want to die in a hospital.

144
00:09:17,400 --> 00:09:18,400
Mae...

145
00:09:29,905 --> 00:09:31,185
Gently now.

146
00:09:31,997 --> 00:09:33,011
Okay.

147
00:09:36,560 --> 00:09:38,040
Thank you, Nidnoi.

148
00:09:50,026 --> 00:09:51,320
Any luck?

149
00:09:51,960 --> 00:09:54,720
I heard she hasn't been in touch
with her relatives for ages.

150
00:09:55,200 --> 00:09:56,360
It's hard to believe.

151
00:09:56,935 --> 00:09:59,280
She really must have been
out of touch for a long time.

152
00:09:59,800 --> 00:10:03,840
All the mobile numbers
in here start with 01.

153
00:10:04,080 --> 00:10:06,920
And they only have
nine digits in total.

154
00:10:10,032 --> 00:10:13,200
All the landline numbers
are disconnected.

155
00:10:14,876 --> 00:10:16,280
And these letters...

156
00:10:16,758 --> 00:10:19,520
they're just
rejection letters from jobs

157
00:10:20,262 --> 00:10:23,160
and overdue bills
for water and electricity.

158
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:28,200
So how are we going to
contact her relatives?

159
00:10:49,182 --> 00:10:51,868
Is this the only photo you have?

160
00:10:52,562 --> 00:10:53,782
Mmm...

161
00:10:54,600 --> 00:10:58,600
Mae Champi only said it was taken
at a temple near her home

162
00:10:59,207 --> 00:11:02,047
when she went back
to visit for the last time.

163
00:11:03,233 --> 00:11:05,807
It's black and white
and quite faded, too.

164
00:11:06,280 --> 00:11:08,120
How are we going to
find her relatives?

165
00:11:10,440 --> 00:11:12,963
- Look on the bright side,
- Mmm.

166
00:11:12,963 --> 00:11:17,803
at least we know
where we have to start.

167
00:11:21,200 --> 00:11:23,800
- Countryside?
- Mmm.

168
00:11:25,538 --> 00:11:27,758
Think of it as a chance for us
to go on a trip together.

169
00:11:28,184 --> 00:11:30,370
I knew it.

170
00:11:30,370 --> 00:11:33,297
The way you're looking at me
is giving me goosebumps.

171
00:11:33,297 --> 00:11:35,323
If only I were this lucky
with the lottery.

172
00:11:46,591 --> 00:11:50,138
"Wat Punnaphisarn Dhammararam,
Ubon Ratchathani"

173
00:11:53,071 --> 00:11:54,734
"Wat Punnaphisarn Dhammararam"

174
00:11:56,120 --> 00:11:59,938
Jee, it's definitely this temple.
I'm sure of it.

175
00:12:00,632 --> 00:12:03,320
- Mmm.
- It's exactly the same name.

176
00:12:03,320 --> 00:12:04,320
Mmm.

177
00:12:06,452 --> 00:12:09,360
And are we going to find
her relatives through this temple?

178
00:12:10,772 --> 00:12:12,525
- Why not?
- Hmm?

179
00:12:12,525 --> 00:12:14,018
We'll never know until we try.

180
00:12:16,241 --> 00:12:17,241
Hmm...

181
00:12:25,080 --> 00:12:26,400
Greetings, Luang Por.

182
00:12:27,440 --> 00:12:28,600
Blessings to you.

183
00:12:29,920 --> 00:12:31,400
Luang Por...

184
00:12:33,680 --> 00:12:37,400
Is this the same temple
with the one in this photo?

185
00:12:41,463 --> 00:12:42,823
Yes, it is.

186
00:12:44,908 --> 00:12:49,680
Are there any faces here
that look familiar to you?

187
00:12:51,064 --> 00:12:52,470
They look familiar.

188
00:12:53,230 --> 00:12:55,297
But I don't recognize
the one in the middle.

189
00:12:56,520 --> 00:13:00,500
The one in the middle,
her name is Mae Champi.

190
00:13:02,177 --> 00:13:03,323
I don't know her.

191
00:13:15,592 --> 00:13:17,512
"Her old name was Yodchai."

192
00:13:17,512 --> 00:13:20,085
"People there probably
don't know her new stage name."

193
00:13:23,560 --> 00:13:24,807
Luang Phor...

194
00:13:25,455 --> 00:13:27,560
What about the name Yodchai?

195
00:13:28,083 --> 00:13:29,209
Does that ring a bell?

196
00:13:30,449 --> 00:13:31,496
Right.

197
00:13:31,496 --> 00:13:33,473
Yodchai.

198
00:13:34,756 --> 00:13:36,660
Yes, this is Yodchai.

199
00:13:36,660 --> 00:13:39,606
The youngest of
Grandpa Kham and Grandma Daeng.

200
00:13:42,588 --> 00:13:45,720
Do you happen to know
where their house is?

201
00:13:51,296 --> 00:13:52,351
Hello?

202
00:13:52,808 --> 00:13:55,096
This is the voice of the Abbot.

203
00:13:55,786 --> 00:13:57,899
Greetings to everyone!

204
00:13:57,899 --> 00:14:00,839
I have a matter
for which I need your help.

205
00:14:01,669 --> 00:14:03,922
Does anyone know
or was anyone born in time

206
00:14:03,922 --> 00:14:05,902
to remember
Grandpa Kham and Grandma Daeng?

207
00:14:05,902 --> 00:14:08,496
The ones who had
a feminine child named Yodchai.

208
00:14:08,496 --> 00:14:09,753
If anyone knows them,

209
00:14:09,753 --> 00:14:12,440
please notify me immediately.

210
00:14:12,440 --> 00:14:14,300
This is a matter of life and death.

211
00:14:14,300 --> 00:14:16,480
Anyone who can help

212
00:14:16,480 --> 00:14:19,227
will receive a truly
immense amount of merit.

213
00:14:23,138 --> 00:14:25,171
Is this becoming too big of a deal?

214
00:14:28,993 --> 00:14:31,905
- He is really kind, isn't he?
- Hmm.

215
00:14:49,920 --> 00:14:51,960
Are you sure
we're going the right way?

216
00:14:53,320 --> 00:14:55,589
- I don't know.
- What?

217
00:14:56,040 --> 00:14:59,160
I'm just guessing
based on what they told us.

218
00:14:59,711 --> 00:15:02,231
I think if we're lost,
we should just stop and ask

219
00:15:02,231 --> 00:15:06,731
where Yodchai's house is.
How's that sound?

220
00:15:07,371 --> 00:15:08,564
- Good.
- Yeah.

221
00:15:13,173 --> 00:15:16,200
I feel guilty toward
Mae Champi somehow.

222
00:15:17,454 --> 00:15:20,519
- For using her old male name?
- Mmm.

223
00:15:23,920 --> 00:15:26,773
Probably as guilty as

224
00:15:26,773 --> 00:15:31,188
leaving her to stay all alone
in a all-male hospital ward.

225
00:15:32,149 --> 00:15:33,149
Mmm.

226
00:15:39,250 --> 00:15:43,000
Should we stop and ask
that grocery store on the left?

227
00:15:43,397 --> 00:15:45,120
- Shall we?
- Yeah, good idea.

228
00:15:45,740 --> 00:15:50,144
Excuse me, please pull over
at that grocery store on the left.

229
00:15:50,672 --> 00:15:51,672
Real quick.

230
00:15:52,098 --> 00:15:53,391
Right here.

231
00:15:53,699 --> 00:15:54,699
Yes.

232
00:15:57,719 --> 00:15:58,999
- Right here?
- Hmm.

233
00:15:59,805 --> 00:16:00,958
I'll ask her.

234
00:16:02,868 --> 00:16:05,240
- Hello there.
- Hello, dear.

235
00:16:06,080 --> 00:16:07,560
Can I ask you something?

236
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:10,640
Do you happen to
know the house of...

237
00:16:11,880 --> 00:16:12,887
this person?

238
00:16:12,887 --> 00:16:16,780
Yodchai, the son of
Grandpa Kham and Grandma Daeng?

239
00:16:17,884 --> 00:16:20,931
Grandpa Kham and Grandma Daeng
passed away a long time ago.

240
00:16:21,756 --> 00:16:24,840
After they died,
the family sold off their land,

241
00:16:24,840 --> 00:16:26,520
and moved to the outskirts of town.

242
00:16:26,520 --> 00:16:28,701
- Moved?
- Yes.

243
00:16:30,240 --> 00:16:31,360
The whole family?

244
00:16:31,746 --> 00:16:35,160
Every last one of them.
Not a soul left.

245
00:16:35,828 --> 00:16:39,560
That means we won't be
able to find their relatives then.

246
00:16:45,840 --> 00:16:46,893
You will.

247
00:16:48,612 --> 00:16:49,612
Really?

248
00:16:59,400 --> 00:17:00,880
Turn right here.

249
00:17:07,183 --> 00:17:08,423
You can pull over here.

250
00:17:09,080 --> 00:17:10,353
Right here is fine.

251
00:17:11,480 --> 00:17:12,480
Thank you.

252
00:17:13,571 --> 00:17:16,051
Here we are. Come on.

253
00:17:16,051 --> 00:17:17,367
Thank you.

254
00:17:17,969 --> 00:17:19,560
Let's see if this is it.

255
00:17:21,325 --> 00:17:24,400
Kru Somchai's House.
Hey, awesome!

256
00:17:24,400 --> 00:17:27,627
This is it, Kru Somchai's house.

257
00:17:27,627 --> 00:17:29,660
She pinned the location perfectly.

258
00:17:30,640 --> 00:17:32,160
That lady was the real deal.

259
00:17:32,674 --> 00:17:37,301
You've got to be smart
to run a grocery store!

260
00:17:37,301 --> 00:17:40,400
Well, are you ready,
Son of a Shopkeeper?

261
00:17:42,153 --> 00:17:43,293
I guess.

262
00:17:44,189 --> 00:17:49,314
But is this really
her nephew's house?

263
00:17:49,314 --> 00:17:51,280
I don't know. Let's find out.

264
00:17:53,055 --> 00:17:54,135
Let's go.

265
00:18:15,141 --> 00:18:16,315
Here.

266
00:18:27,878 --> 00:18:28,878
Have some water.

267
00:18:29,488 --> 00:18:30,680
Thank you very much.

268
00:18:38,320 --> 00:18:39,640
Looking at this,

269
00:18:40,550 --> 00:18:41,813
it sounds about right.

270
00:18:42,456 --> 00:18:43,939
This is my grandfather.

271
00:18:45,236 --> 00:18:48,029
And this is my grandmother.

272
00:18:49,939 --> 00:18:51,939
But the one in the middle,

273
00:18:52,715 --> 00:18:54,715
I'm not sure

274
00:18:55,946 --> 00:18:57,415
whether he is my uncle or not

275
00:18:58,332 --> 00:19:00,332
because we have never met before.

276
00:19:01,427 --> 00:19:02,480
I see.

277
00:19:03,505 --> 00:19:07,458
Previously, your uncle

278
00:19:07,458 --> 00:19:09,440
went by the name Yodchai.

279
00:19:10,226 --> 00:19:13,680
But nowadays,
she has changed it to Champi.

280
00:19:13,680 --> 00:19:16,040
Oh, that's why...

281
00:19:17,223 --> 00:19:20,597
My dad told me he had
a brother who was transgender.

282
00:19:21,653 --> 00:19:23,593
Grandpa used to spank him
when he was young.

283
00:19:24,770 --> 00:19:28,223
When he grew up,
he got kicked out of the house.

284
00:19:28,223 --> 00:19:30,383
- Mmm.
- I didn't think...

285
00:19:31,407 --> 00:19:33,770
he would have a photo

286
00:19:34,466 --> 00:19:35,853
dressed as a man like this.

287
00:19:36,273 --> 00:19:40,280
And you've never met
Mae Champi even once?

288
00:19:44,263 --> 00:19:45,399
Never.

289
00:19:46,822 --> 00:19:52,162
My dad hardly ever
talked about him.

290
00:20:09,047 --> 00:20:10,047
Mmm.

291
00:20:12,148 --> 00:20:13,280
Thanks a lot, Thai.

292
00:20:17,600 --> 00:20:18,600
Ohn is calling.

293
00:20:19,758 --> 00:20:20,758
Answer it.

294
00:20:21,920 --> 00:20:22,920
Hello?

295
00:20:23,920 --> 00:20:25,200
Really?

296
00:20:25,680 --> 00:20:29,200
I'll put you on speaker.
So Mom can hear, too.

297
00:20:30,595 --> 00:20:31,595
There.

298
00:20:33,165 --> 00:20:35,291
- Go ahead.
- Mae Champi,

299
00:20:35,291 --> 00:20:37,898
there's no one left
at your old house.

300
00:20:39,480 --> 00:20:42,680
Of course no one's left.
They're probably all dead by now.

301
00:20:43,425 --> 00:20:48,080
Don't underestimate me.
This is Ohn we're talking about.

302
00:20:48,913 --> 00:20:52,560
I actually found
your brother's house.

303
00:20:52,560 --> 00:20:54,387
Ohn, you're the absolute best.

304
00:20:56,799 --> 00:20:58,496
Why go looking for them?

305
00:20:59,348 --> 00:21:01,680
My brother is likely dead by now.

306
00:21:02,280 --> 00:21:04,819
You're spot on.

307
00:21:04,819 --> 00:21:07,604
- Your brother has passed away.
- Oh.

308
00:21:07,604 --> 00:21:12,280
But the rest of his family,
they're still around.

309
00:21:17,080 --> 00:21:18,080
No.

310
00:21:19,303 --> 00:21:21,280
I'm not going anywhere.

311
00:21:21,965 --> 00:21:24,978
I'm not going! No, no, no...

312
00:21:24,978 --> 00:21:29,058
I'm not going anywhere!

313
00:21:29,058 --> 00:21:30,638
I don't want to go.

314
00:21:30,638 --> 00:21:31,868
Mae, just go.

315
00:21:31,868 --> 00:21:33,987
Ohn has talked to them. Please.

316
00:21:35,591 --> 00:21:36,738
We all go with you.

317
00:21:36,738 --> 00:21:40,351
Leave me alone. I don't want to go.

318
00:21:40,351 --> 00:21:42,560
- Mae, please go.
- Please, Mom?

319
00:21:43,440 --> 00:21:45,518
- Please, Mom.
- Let's go.

320
00:21:45,960 --> 00:21:47,080
- Please?
- Please?

321
00:21:48,360 --> 00:21:49,720
Lay down.

322
00:21:54,840 --> 00:21:58,800
No, I'm not going!

323
00:22:01,593 --> 00:22:04,788
I'm not going anywhere!

324
00:22:05,440 --> 00:22:06,913
Is this really a good idea?

325
00:22:08,120 --> 00:22:09,120
Jee...

326
00:22:10,340 --> 00:22:13,333
Do you really think I wouldn't
choose what's best for Mae Champi?

327
00:22:14,480 --> 00:22:19,453
Being with her relatives
is the best care for her.

328
00:22:25,221 --> 00:22:26,280
Okay.

329
00:22:27,177 --> 00:22:29,000
If you say so, I'm with you.

330
00:22:34,607 --> 00:22:35,880
Ouu...

331
00:22:36,240 --> 00:22:37,720
Mae, stay still for a moment.

332
00:22:38,228 --> 00:22:39,441
Hmm...

333
00:22:39,441 --> 00:22:41,640
- Exhausted?
- Very much so.

334
00:22:43,568 --> 00:22:44,568
Ouu...

335
00:22:46,443 --> 00:22:49,520
Ohn, Jira, take me home!

336
00:22:50,126 --> 00:22:51,866
Take me home, Ohn.

337
00:22:51,866 --> 00:22:56,933
Who's going to believe she's sick
with this non-stop nagging?

338
00:22:56,933 --> 00:22:58,693
She's been complaining
the entire way here.

339
00:22:58,693 --> 00:23:00,173
I haven't slept at all.

340
00:23:00,173 --> 00:23:02,979
It looks like she really
didn't want to come.

341
00:23:02,979 --> 00:23:06,013
Why are you doing this?

342
00:23:06,013 --> 00:23:08,083
What's happening

343
00:23:08,883 --> 00:23:10,743
We talked about this yesterday.

344
00:23:14,080 --> 00:23:17,341
What if Mae Champi, I mean...

345
00:23:18,849 --> 00:23:20,200
Uncle Yodchai,

346
00:23:20,911 --> 00:23:22,520
well, I mean Mae Champi,

347
00:23:24,000 --> 00:23:26,040
were to come back here,

348
00:23:27,030 --> 00:23:28,720
how would everyone here
feel about that?

349
00:23:36,904 --> 00:23:38,797
If we could see each other

350
00:23:38,797 --> 00:23:40,531
before passing away,

351
00:23:40,531 --> 00:23:42,075
then it would be alright.

352
00:23:43,104 --> 00:23:45,960
After all, we are relatives.

353
00:23:46,711 --> 00:23:48,711
It doesn't hurt
to get to know one another.

354
00:23:49,027 --> 00:23:50,173
Yes.

355
00:23:51,678 --> 00:23:53,745
Let me see.

356
00:23:53,745 --> 00:23:55,987
- This is Grandma.
- She's so beautiful.

357
00:23:57,558 --> 00:23:58,938
And this must be him.

358
00:24:00,937 --> 00:24:03,204
Ohn, take me home!

359
00:24:03,204 --> 00:24:04,997
Take me home!

360
00:24:04,997 --> 00:24:06,400
Ohn! Ohn!

361
00:24:07,211 --> 00:24:09,298
Ohn, are you going to
abandon me here?

362
00:24:09,298 --> 00:24:11,598
Take me home!

363
00:24:11,598 --> 00:24:13,617
Stay here with your grandkids.

364
00:24:14,552 --> 00:24:17,592
They'll take great care of you.
They are family.

365
00:24:22,183 --> 00:24:24,469
- Which way should I take her?
- Right inside, please.

366
00:24:26,354 --> 00:24:27,354
Okay.

367
00:24:36,070 --> 00:24:38,743
Dad, who is this?

368
00:24:40,580 --> 00:24:43,013
What I said yesterday was that

369
00:24:43,756 --> 00:24:45,957
If it's a visit to see each other,

370
00:24:45,957 --> 00:24:47,237
I don't object to that.

371
00:24:48,168 --> 00:24:50,707
But not to have him move in
and become a burden like this.

372
00:24:51,282 --> 00:24:52,435
- What?
- What?

373
00:24:54,000 --> 00:24:56,340
Why did you say
they were okay with it?

374
00:24:57,160 --> 00:25:00,308
I thought they were.

375
00:25:00,605 --> 00:25:01,605
No.

376
00:25:03,718 --> 00:25:05,532
Not okay at all.

377
00:25:05,532 --> 00:25:08,739
Well, in that case...

378
00:25:08,739 --> 00:25:11,452
since Mae Champi is already here

379
00:25:11,452 --> 00:25:14,872
why don't you go talk to her
and get to know her?

380
00:25:14,872 --> 00:25:18,339
She is your father's
younger sibling, after all.

381
00:25:18,339 --> 00:25:20,312
Getting to know each other
would be great, right?

382
00:25:20,312 --> 00:25:22,318
Yeah, just have a chat.

383
00:25:24,626 --> 00:25:26,019
Well, I did talk to him.

384
00:25:26,720 --> 00:25:28,200
How exactly did you talk to him?

385
00:25:28,935 --> 00:25:32,128
We were just talking casually,
and he said it was okay.

386
00:25:35,657 --> 00:25:38,960
I have to admit that you did well
on finding this temple.

387
00:25:45,360 --> 00:25:48,280
The temple has a nickname,
so it was easy to find.

388
00:25:48,631 --> 00:25:51,760
It's an old name, not a nickname.

389
00:25:51,760 --> 00:25:53,093
Yeah, whatever.

390
00:25:55,580 --> 00:25:58,227
And I'm officially
taking back my applause.

391
00:25:58,227 --> 00:26:00,800
Because you clearly miscommunicated
with Mae Champi's relatives.

392
00:26:03,640 --> 00:26:06,280
Fine, fine. It's my fault.

393
00:26:06,972 --> 00:26:08,425
I wasn't being thorough.

394
00:26:08,425 --> 00:26:12,972
It was a mix of me being hopeful
and fantasizing on my own

395
00:26:12,972 --> 00:26:15,080
that relatives who have never met

396
00:26:15,832 --> 00:26:17,992
could meet during
the final stage of life

397
00:26:17,992 --> 00:26:20,998
and care for each other.
I thought it would be touching.

398
00:26:23,432 --> 00:26:25,952
But if it were me,
and a stranger came up and said

399
00:26:25,952 --> 00:26:29,012
they were an uncle, aunt,
or some distant relative,

400
00:26:29,012 --> 00:26:31,758
I'd have to think long and hard.
I wouldn't help immediately.

401
00:26:32,240 --> 00:26:34,480
- Oh, really?
- It means we...

402
00:26:35,723 --> 00:26:38,814
were too naive, right?
We didn't think it through.

403
00:26:39,736 --> 00:26:41,996
What do we do now?

404
00:26:45,920 --> 00:26:47,461
Should we try to find

405
00:26:47,461 --> 00:26:50,954
a nursing home that
provides palliative care?

406
00:26:51,800 --> 00:26:53,746
And we all split the costs?

407
00:26:55,267 --> 00:26:56,800
How much would that be per month?

408
00:26:57,885 --> 00:27:00,710
It's quite a lot of money.

409
00:27:02,013 --> 00:27:03,153
And...

410
00:27:03,153 --> 00:27:08,680
Jee is unemployed too,
so we have to save money.

411
00:27:10,120 --> 00:27:12,960
I'm sorry.

412
00:27:14,000 --> 00:27:15,600
Don't worry about it.

413
00:27:16,460 --> 00:27:20,206
Mae Champi probably wouldn't
let us pay for her anyway.

414
00:27:26,264 --> 00:27:29,291
Nam Pla, Nam Tan, wash your hands
and come have your dinner.

415
00:27:29,777 --> 00:27:32,360
- Yes...
- Listen to that!

416
00:27:33,550 --> 00:27:35,550
Go ahead. Please enjoy.

417
00:27:39,703 --> 00:27:41,480
Here they are.

418
00:27:43,695 --> 00:27:46,275
Here are Larb and Namtok, everyone!

419
00:27:46,275 --> 00:27:47,335
Here we go.

420
00:27:48,516 --> 00:27:49,696
- Oh!
- Grandma! Grandma!

421
00:27:49,696 --> 00:27:51,924
- Mae! Mae!
- Napkins.

422
00:27:53,454 --> 00:27:54,633
Here.

423
00:27:55,324 --> 00:27:57,120
- Napkins.
- Mae.

424
00:27:59,300 --> 00:28:00,367
Hold this here.

425
00:28:05,278 --> 00:28:07,080
- Easy.
- Careful with your steps.

426
00:28:12,749 --> 00:28:14,397
Uncle Yodchai and I, I mean...

427
00:28:14,980 --> 00:28:17,063
Aunt Champi, we've never even met.

428
00:28:17,660 --> 00:28:19,226
We're basically strangers.

429
00:28:19,916 --> 00:28:23,729
To have us take care of her
while she's sick...

430
00:28:24,484 --> 00:28:26,060
is a lot to ask, you know?

431
00:28:28,564 --> 00:28:29,923
I'm retired myself.

432
00:28:30,613 --> 00:28:33,576
I rely on my kids to look after me
and take me to the doctor.

433
00:28:34,420 --> 00:28:39,326
If I were to make them take on
the burden of caring for her,

434
00:28:40,582 --> 00:28:42,582
I'd feel bad for my kids, too.

435
00:28:46,698 --> 00:28:47,698
Yes.

436
00:28:48,730 --> 00:28:52,284
Anyway, I have to thank you.

437
00:28:56,183 --> 00:28:58,800
We are heading back now.

438
00:29:01,671 --> 00:29:02,788
- Goodbye.
- Goodbye.

439
00:29:02,788 --> 00:29:03,918
Goodbye, children.

440
00:29:04,441 --> 00:29:05,861
Safe travels!

441
00:29:06,282 --> 00:29:07,321
Thank you.

442
00:29:14,549 --> 00:29:15,640
Grandma...

443
00:29:20,480 --> 00:29:22,440
- Goodbye.
- Goodbye.

444
00:29:48,960 --> 00:29:49,960
Mae…

445
00:29:53,473 --> 00:29:54,733
I'm sorry.

446
00:29:55,080 --> 00:29:58,000
For not talkin to you first
before bringing you here.

447
00:30:00,369 --> 00:30:01,369
Mmm.

448
00:30:02,989 --> 00:30:04,560
I'm not angry, Ohn.

449
00:30:05,527 --> 00:30:07,440
I know you had good intentions.

450
00:30:08,520 --> 00:30:10,915
You wanted my relatives
to take care of me.

451
00:30:12,000 --> 00:30:14,000
That's exactly what I thought.

452
00:30:15,520 --> 00:30:18,400
I never intended
to just abandon you.

453
00:30:20,724 --> 00:30:21,791
Mmm.

454
00:30:24,629 --> 00:30:26,708
Ever since I left home...

455
00:30:28,583 --> 00:30:31,360
I never contacted them again.

456
00:30:33,360 --> 00:30:35,480
I never asked for help.

457
00:30:37,069 --> 00:30:39,640
I never got involved
with them at all.

458
00:30:40,800 --> 00:30:43,967
Now that I'm sick,
to ask them to care for me...

459
00:30:43,967 --> 00:30:45,560
I just can't do it.

460
00:30:46,569 --> 00:30:48,709
It would ruin the dignity
of an old queen like me.

461
00:30:50,210 --> 00:30:55,200
I'd rather die alone
in my own home.

462
00:30:58,223 --> 00:30:59,560
Not a chance.

463
00:31:00,013 --> 00:31:01,086
Hmm?

464
00:31:03,040 --> 00:31:04,480
Who could ever
let you be like that?

465
00:31:05,160 --> 00:31:06,160
Right, guys?

466
00:31:18,113 --> 00:31:20,720
You guys, I think...

467
00:31:21,261 --> 00:31:22,261
What?

468
00:31:22,902 --> 00:31:25,640
We were able to grow and
be proud of our identities

469
00:31:26,080 --> 00:31:28,467
because we had
Mae Champi as our life guide.

470
00:31:28,467 --> 00:31:29,493
Mmm.

471
00:31:30,298 --> 00:31:32,720
She's not a relative,
but she's just like family.

472
00:31:34,520 --> 00:31:37,560
So, all of us, the Fab Family,

473
00:31:38,427 --> 00:31:40,360
we take turns looking after her?

474
00:31:40,360 --> 00:31:41,560
Mmm.

475
00:31:42,720 --> 00:31:44,540
We'll provide her
with palliative care.

476
00:31:44,540 --> 00:31:47,440
Let her go peacefully,
just the way she wants.

477
00:31:48,023 --> 00:31:49,063
- Mmm.
- Mmm.

478
00:31:58,560 --> 00:32:00,200
Take care of Mae Champi!

479
00:32:00,693 --> 00:32:01,693
- Yay!
- Yay!

480
00:32:04,785 --> 00:32:10,014
And do you guys know how to
provide the palliative care?

481
00:32:14,633 --> 00:32:15,753
Oh...

482
00:32:32,320 --> 00:32:33,360
It's nice and hot.

483
00:32:34,174 --> 00:32:35,320
Thank you, dear.

484
00:32:35,768 --> 00:32:36,901
Eat it all up, okay?

485
00:33:03,502 --> 00:33:04,788
Time for your medicine.

486
00:33:29,476 --> 00:33:33,090
Your lips are looking a bit pale.

487
00:33:34,004 --> 00:33:35,177
Want some lipstick?

488
00:33:38,895 --> 00:33:41,840
Here, you can choose.
Which color do you want?

489
00:33:42,293 --> 00:33:45,960
Purple? Or maybe this pink one?

490
00:33:52,086 --> 00:33:53,153
Beautiful.

491
00:33:57,105 --> 00:33:59,080
- Beautiful now?
- Beautiful.

492
00:34:05,906 --> 00:34:08,681
- Hello! Take care.
- Hello!

493
00:34:57,480 --> 00:34:58,560
Careful, Mae.

494
00:35:02,873 --> 00:35:04,329
Look at you...

495
00:35:04,329 --> 00:35:07,242
You cry every time
you go to care for her.

496
00:35:07,242 --> 00:35:08,968
Can you handle this?

497
00:35:10,046 --> 00:35:14,280
With palliative care,
the caregivers must be okay, too.

498
00:35:17,910 --> 00:35:20,600
When I think about it,
it hits home.

499
00:35:21,902 --> 00:35:23,102
I think about the time...

500
00:35:24,595 --> 00:35:26,000
when I just assumed that...

501
00:35:27,329 --> 00:35:31,080
her relatives would be
the ones to take care of her.

502
00:35:32,364 --> 00:35:36,360
Without even asking
for Mae Champi's consent.

503
00:35:38,196 --> 00:35:39,196
Yeah, true.

504
00:35:40,321 --> 00:35:42,560
It's her life, her body.

505
00:35:43,578 --> 00:35:46,138
She should have a part
in the decision-making, right?

506
00:35:49,920 --> 00:35:52,086
So, what if...

507
00:35:53,600 --> 00:35:56,160
If I get old and
have no one to care for me...

508
00:35:57,000 --> 00:35:58,138
Wait a second.

509
00:35:58,138 --> 00:36:01,698
We were just talking
about palliative care.

510
00:36:01,698 --> 00:36:03,364
How did we end up on this topic?

511
00:36:03,970 --> 00:36:05,170
Hmm?

512
00:36:05,170 --> 00:36:09,223
You have me.
We'll take care of each other.

513
00:36:10,360 --> 00:36:11,680
But what if we break up?

514
00:36:13,069 --> 00:36:14,069
Hey!

515
00:36:16,683 --> 00:36:19,743
Are you still believing
in that 7-year itch jinx?

516
00:36:19,743 --> 00:36:22,029
You believe the fortune teller
more than you trust me?

517
00:36:23,911 --> 00:36:25,720
- It's not that.
- Mmm.

518
00:36:26,229 --> 00:36:29,440
When I'm anxious, my mind wanders.

519
00:36:33,520 --> 00:36:35,086
What if between the two of us...

520
00:36:37,320 --> 00:36:39,687
someone has to go first,

521
00:36:39,687 --> 00:36:43,461
leaving the other all alone?

522
00:36:46,143 --> 00:36:48,680
How about we wait until that day
before we start worrying?

523
00:36:50,909 --> 00:36:54,902
Just know that, today and tomorrow,
we are here for each other.

524
00:36:57,445 --> 00:36:59,614
Mmm...

525
00:37:00,512 --> 00:37:01,592
You know...

526
00:37:02,958 --> 00:37:05,200
Just worrying about
Mae Champi is enough.

527
00:37:06,427 --> 00:37:07,567
Got it?

528
00:37:08,208 --> 00:37:09,208
Good.

529
00:37:15,691 --> 00:37:20,440
Jee! How could you fart right now?
I was having a moment!

530
00:37:20,440 --> 00:37:23,440
That's your punishment
for worrying too much.

531
00:37:24,064 --> 00:37:25,633
Eww...

532
00:37:26,990 --> 00:37:29,106
What did you have for dinner?

533
00:37:29,839 --> 00:37:31,120
Is something rotting inside you?

534
00:37:31,987 --> 00:37:36,247
Charcoal, come sleep with me?

535
00:37:36,247 --> 00:37:39,823
Look, Daddy Ohn is acting
all grossed out by Papa's fart.

536
00:37:40,384 --> 00:37:43,080
You aren't grossed out, right?
Come here.

537
00:37:44,120 --> 00:37:46,024
Charcoal probably can't
smell anything by now.

538
00:37:46,024 --> 00:37:48,820
Come sleep right here.

539
00:37:48,820 --> 00:37:50,293
Ugh...

540
00:37:50,293 --> 00:37:52,160
Stop fanning!

541
00:37:52,546 --> 00:37:53,967
Come on, Charcoal.

542
00:38:06,421 --> 00:38:08,600
Thai, how is she doing?

543
00:38:09,535 --> 00:38:12,415
Her condition is stable.

544
00:38:14,120 --> 00:38:16,048
She's been sleeping a lot lately.

545
00:38:16,048 --> 00:38:17,948
For very long stretch each time.

546
00:38:17,948 --> 00:38:19,114
But it's good, actually.

547
00:38:19,114 --> 00:38:21,841
When she's asleep,
she isn't in pain.

548
00:38:28,881 --> 00:38:30,517
- A little more.
- No more.

549
00:38:30,517 --> 00:38:31,903
- One more bite?
- That's enough.

550
00:38:45,960 --> 00:38:47,387
I'm so sorry, Mindy.

551
00:38:47,387 --> 00:38:50,486
I really haven't had any time
to think about anything else.

552
00:38:50,960 --> 00:38:52,466
Let's just get through this first.

553
00:38:53,246 --> 00:38:55,800
Yeah, thank you so much, Mindy.

554
00:39:01,280 --> 00:39:03,400
If you're so busy,
you don't have to be here.

555
00:39:03,920 --> 00:39:06,560
Having you guys here every day,
it's annoying.

556
00:39:09,000 --> 00:39:10,093
Mae.

557
00:39:10,778 --> 00:39:13,960
You might be annoyed, but I'm not.

558
00:39:17,760 --> 00:39:21,293
If you're worried about work,
you don't need to stay.

559
00:39:21,840 --> 00:39:24,400
I can take care of myself.

560
00:39:26,029 --> 00:39:27,240
Mae, please...

561
00:39:27,943 --> 00:39:31,720
I just want to spend
as much time with you as possible.

562
00:39:33,240 --> 00:39:34,689
Please don't chase me away.

563
00:39:35,280 --> 00:39:37,000
I can work anytime.

564
00:39:38,240 --> 00:39:40,680
Besides, it's not like...

565
00:39:41,800 --> 00:39:44,120
it sells well anyway.

566
00:39:45,637 --> 00:39:47,600
I'm just a struggling artist.

567
00:39:52,174 --> 00:39:55,933
I bought some Som Tum
and grilled chicken for you.

568
00:39:55,933 --> 00:39:57,000
See?

569
00:39:57,800 --> 00:40:00,104
I can't have spicy Som Tum.

570
00:40:01,788 --> 00:40:02,788
Oh...

571
00:40:03,374 --> 00:40:07,234
Didn't you say you were
bored of congee and bland food?

572
00:40:07,234 --> 00:40:10,000
Let's switch it up
to some zesty Som Tum.

573
00:40:11,040 --> 00:40:12,540
I don't want it. Just take it back.

574
00:40:12,540 --> 00:40:14,200
What?

575
00:40:15,000 --> 00:40:16,200
What's the matter?

576
00:40:17,747 --> 00:40:20,920
If you didn't want Som Tum,
you could have just told me.

577
00:40:21,520 --> 00:40:22,520
I don't want it.

578
00:40:23,372 --> 00:40:26,142
I don't want anything.
Just take it all away!

579
00:40:26,623 --> 00:40:28,080
And go back to work!

580
00:40:40,251 --> 00:40:41,360
Are you back, Jee?

581
00:40:41,680 --> 00:40:46,360
Yes, I am home.

582
00:40:47,958 --> 00:40:50,560
I'm back.

583
00:40:53,628 --> 00:40:54,628
Oh.

584
00:40:55,448 --> 00:40:58,101
It's late and
you're just now eating?

585
00:40:58,101 --> 00:41:01,821
I bought Som Tum for Mae Champi.

586
00:41:01,821 --> 00:41:03,078
Mmm-hmm.

587
00:41:03,906 --> 00:41:06,051
- But she wouldn't eat it.
- Oh?

588
00:41:06,051 --> 00:41:08,206
So I brought it back.

589
00:41:08,736 --> 00:41:10,320
I was going to eat it at home.

590
00:41:10,842 --> 00:41:13,842
But it's gone stale and soggy.

591
00:41:13,842 --> 00:41:15,807
So I'm having this noodles instead.

592
00:41:16,400 --> 00:41:17,438
Mmm.

593
00:41:17,438 --> 00:41:19,105
What about you? Hungry?

594
00:41:19,105 --> 00:41:23,600
Mom cooked so much food.
I'm stuffed.

595
00:41:25,000 --> 00:41:27,032
Mom sent you this fish soup, too.

596
00:41:27,032 --> 00:41:28,320
Whoa...

597
00:41:30,680 --> 00:41:33,104
You came a little too late.

598
00:41:33,104 --> 00:41:34,339
Too bad.

599
00:41:35,213 --> 00:41:36,520
About Mae Champi...

600
00:41:37,000 --> 00:41:39,440
Besides not eating, is she being
stubborn about anything else?

601
00:41:40,113 --> 00:41:42,133
Chon and Thai said that

602
00:41:42,133 --> 00:41:45,480
She's been sleeping more,

603
00:41:46,240 --> 00:41:47,420
eating less,

604
00:41:48,043 --> 00:41:49,346
and getting irritable easily.

605
00:41:50,080 --> 00:41:53,240
Her pain is getting worse, too.

606
00:41:55,920 --> 00:41:57,433
Nidnoi said that...

607
00:41:57,922 --> 00:42:01,320
She probably doesn't
have much time left.

608
00:42:07,080 --> 00:42:11,080
Does she have
any lingering worries?

609
00:42:43,133 --> 00:42:47,186
You Fabs look as mopey as
a queen without her lipstick.

610
00:42:48,098 --> 00:42:50,747
But you sound so happy!

611
00:42:50,747 --> 00:42:54,480
Is it because
the whole Fab team's here together?

612
00:42:58,571 --> 00:43:01,320
It's good that you're all here.

613
00:43:02,273 --> 00:43:03,840
I have something to give you all.

614
00:43:23,760 --> 00:43:25,720
I don't have many belongings.

615
00:43:26,640 --> 00:43:30,240
But I want you all
to keep them as mementos.

616
00:43:33,000 --> 00:43:35,560
Some I'll give to the neighbor.

617
00:43:36,480 --> 00:43:38,920
And the landlord is very kind.

618
00:43:40,240 --> 00:43:41,840
Letting me stay here
until my last day.

619
00:43:48,073 --> 00:43:49,306
If you guys won't take them,

620
00:43:49,913 --> 00:43:52,874
then please donate them for me.

621
00:43:54,421 --> 00:43:56,520
Let me pick first, then.

622
00:44:02,969 --> 00:44:06,400
Mae, I'm not taking the amulets.
I'm non-religious.

623
00:44:10,875 --> 00:44:12,702
Well, in that case...

624
00:44:15,441 --> 00:44:17,640
take these karaoke CDs.

625
00:44:18,360 --> 00:44:19,360
Thank you, Mae.

626
00:44:32,599 --> 00:44:34,520
You don't mind these, do you?

627
00:44:34,732 --> 00:44:36,520
Not at all. Thank you.

628
00:44:37,120 --> 00:44:38,760
I'll share them with Chon.

629
00:44:41,566 --> 00:44:44,000
I'm taking the lipsticks
and the bag too.

630
00:44:46,050 --> 00:44:49,303
I knew you would love the bags.

631
00:44:49,303 --> 00:44:51,400
Take them all.

632
00:44:56,488 --> 00:44:57,488
Ohn.

633
00:45:02,446 --> 00:45:04,152
For you, it has to be these novels.

634
00:45:06,659 --> 00:45:07,680
Mae...

635
00:45:08,583 --> 00:45:11,200
Don't you want to wait
to read my new comic book?

636
00:45:12,320 --> 00:45:13,320
Of course, I do.

637
00:45:14,664 --> 00:45:16,024
But if I can't...

638
00:45:17,106 --> 00:45:19,272
I'll go read it
in the next life, okay?

639
00:45:35,600 --> 00:45:38,373
There's no need to mourn that much.

640
00:45:38,373 --> 00:45:40,800
I'm just heading on
ahead of you, that's all.

641
00:46:04,100 --> 00:46:05,220
Mae...

642
00:46:06,181 --> 00:46:08,908
I've given all other dolls
to the kids around here.

643
00:46:08,908 --> 00:46:11,600
But I'm keeping
this one for myself.

644
00:46:16,520 --> 00:46:17,520
Mae…

645
00:46:18,824 --> 00:46:21,004
Is there anything
still weighing on your mind?

646
00:46:21,400 --> 00:46:25,280
Anything you want to do,
or to leave for someone?

647
00:46:30,001 --> 00:46:31,594
I have nothing left to leave.

648
00:46:33,313 --> 00:46:35,480
Nothing is weighing on me anymore.

649
00:46:40,689 --> 00:46:41,826
- Mae!
- Mae!

650
00:46:42,877 --> 00:46:44,360
Not yet, not yet!

651
00:46:48,160 --> 00:46:50,480
- But I want to see a show.
- What?

652
00:46:52,360 --> 00:46:54,000
Are you ready?

653
00:46:54,320 --> 00:46:55,947
I'm ready, my children.

654
00:46:55,947 --> 00:46:58,280
Let's put on the crown first.

655
00:46:59,047 --> 00:47:01,673
Put on your crown first,
beautiful Queen.

656
00:47:24,216 --> 00:47:28,840
♪ You are the light
that shines so bright ♪

657
00:47:29,280 --> 00:47:33,760
♪ You are the hope echoing inside ♪

658
00:47:34,295 --> 00:47:38,413
♪ You are the reason
I find the morning light ♪

659
00:47:38,413 --> 00:47:42,773
♪ You are the reason
I find the morning light ♪

660
00:47:51,843 --> 00:47:54,400
Three, four, yay!

661
00:47:54,781 --> 00:47:56,200
Spectrum Fabulous!

662
00:48:06,111 --> 00:48:08,040
- Hello.
- Oh, Jee!

663
00:48:08,040 --> 00:48:09,720
Mae Champi, hello.

664
00:48:09,720 --> 00:48:13,620
- Oh, mmm...
- Come watch them.

665
00:48:15,600 --> 00:48:18,900
- Jee, come join the show!
- What?

666
00:48:18,900 --> 00:48:20,633
Alright, let's do it!

667
00:48:20,633 --> 00:48:22,400
- Yay!
- Yay!

668
00:48:39,334 --> 00:48:42,647
Woo... Woo...

669
00:49:16,137 --> 00:49:17,917
Smile, everyone!

670
00:49:18,708 --> 00:49:20,760
One, two, three, shoot!

671
00:49:21,168 --> 00:49:23,240
One, two, three, shoot!

672
00:49:32,086 --> 00:49:33,540
Are you sure about this, Thai?

673
00:49:36,533 --> 00:49:37,666
Mmm...

674
00:49:38,591 --> 00:49:40,120
Just once in my life.

675
00:50:19,456 --> 00:50:21,680
Ohn, I must give props to...

676
00:50:23,142 --> 00:50:24,309
the monk.

677
00:50:24,749 --> 00:50:27,495
A non-religious person
got ordained for the funeral?

678
00:50:29,360 --> 00:50:31,840
Mae Champi would be so happy.

679
00:50:34,120 --> 00:50:37,200
May Mae Champi
receive Monk Thai's merit,

680
00:50:37,200 --> 00:50:39,840
and take an elevator
to the highest levels of heaven.

681
00:50:39,840 --> 00:50:42,047
- Amen to that.
- Amen to that.

682
00:50:42,047 --> 00:50:45,401
Wait, are there
elevators in heaven?

683
00:50:45,880 --> 00:50:47,360
Come on.

684
00:50:48,068 --> 00:50:50,315
These days, everything has evolved.

685
00:50:50,315 --> 00:50:52,240
Shouldn't heaven
be modernized, too?

686
00:50:52,768 --> 00:50:55,040
- Mmm-hmm.
- Right, Ikkyu?

687
00:50:56,308 --> 00:50:57,601
That's right, Uncle Ohn.

688
00:50:58,545 --> 00:50:59,811
That's my baby!

689
00:51:36,046 --> 00:51:39,400
"As for my funeral,
don't make a big fuss."

690
00:51:41,624 --> 00:51:43,200
"Keep it simple."

691
00:51:46,160 --> 00:51:50,580
"Don't be too somber."

692
00:51:50,580 --> 00:51:53,353
"Or everyone will
end up feeling gloomy."

693
00:51:58,693 --> 00:52:00,560
"Dress in beautiful clothes."

694
00:52:03,488 --> 00:52:05,480
"Celebrate my life."

695
00:52:06,586 --> 00:52:08,460
"Life has suffering,
and it has happiness."

696
00:52:09,680 --> 00:52:11,880
"I'm happy
with the life I've lived."

697
00:52:13,160 --> 00:52:14,240
"And I'm happy..."

698
00:52:15,204 --> 00:52:16,977
"that I got to meet all of you."

699
00:52:54,280 --> 00:52:55,880
Bye-bye!

700
00:53:01,200 --> 00:53:02,680
Hey, Fabs!

701
00:53:03,520 --> 00:53:05,120
Come here!

702
00:53:07,200 --> 00:53:08,373
Queen...

703
00:53:58,765 --> 00:54:00,465
Surrounded by all of you...

704
00:54:05,305 --> 00:54:09,440
even if this dream never ends...

705
00:54:12,077 --> 00:54:13,560
it truly is wonderful.

706
00:54:21,698 --> 00:54:23,138
Thank you.

707
00:55:10,260 --> 00:55:11,717
When that time comes...

708
00:55:11,717 --> 00:55:13,741
if you have to prolong my life...

709
00:55:15,905 --> 00:55:17,292
you have to let me go.

710
00:55:17,292 --> 00:55:18,480
You can't do that!

711
00:55:19,040 --> 00:55:22,680
My son isn't even dead yet.
How can you pull the plug?

712
00:55:22,680 --> 00:55:26,820
- Do you even have a heart?
- Please calm down.

713
00:55:26,820 --> 00:55:28,258
You are an outsider.

714
00:55:28,258 --> 00:55:29,932
You have no rights
to make any decisions.

715
00:55:29,932 --> 00:55:30,965
Understand?

716
00:55:31,920 --> 00:55:33,063
In the end, it's just...

717
00:55:34,125 --> 00:55:37,400
in this life,
have we ever loved someone?

718
00:55:38,080 --> 00:55:40,187
And have we truly been loved
by someone in return?

719
00:55:40,187 --> 00:55:41,600
Isn't that all there is to it?

720
00:55:41,625 --> 00:55:45,570
♪ Can you feel
the stories we made? ♪

721
00:55:45,570 --> 00:55:50,499
♪ No matter what stood in our way ♪

722
00:55:50,499 --> 00:55:53,993
♪ Come rain or shine ♪
Subtitle by Trirat Trakulphat
